#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn53.1-12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 53 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 53 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:0.2"
msgid "1. Gaṅgāpeyyālavagga "
msgstr "1. Abbreviated Texts on the Ganges "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 1–12. Jhānādisutta → pathamasuddhiyaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:0.3"
msgid "1–12. Jhānādisutta "
msgstr "1–12. Absorptions, Etc. "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.307, sc1
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho … pe … "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:1.3"
msgid "“cattārome, bhikkhave, jhānā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four absorptions. "

msgctxt "sn53.1-12:1.4"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:1.5"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:1.6"
msgid "Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:1.7"
msgid "Pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "And with the fading away of rapture, they enter and remain in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:1.8"
msgid "Sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, they enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:1.9"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro jhānāti. "
msgstr "These are the four absorptions. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.308, sc2
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gaṅgā nadī pācīnaninnā pācīnapoṇā pācīnapabbhārā; "
msgstr "The Ganges river slants, slopes, and inclines to the east. "

msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.2"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāro jhāne bhāvento cattāro jhāne bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro. "
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant who develops and cultivates the four absorptions slants, slopes, and inclines to extinguishment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.3"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāro jhāne bhāvento cattāro jhāne bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro? "
msgstr "And how does a mendicant who develops and cultivates the four absorptions slant, slope, and incline to extinguishment? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.4"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.5"
msgid "Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … "
msgstr "As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption … "

msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.6"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … "
msgstr "third absorption … "

msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.7"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "fourth absorption. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.8"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cattāro jhāne bhāvento cattāro jhāne bahulīkaronto nibbānaninno hoti nibbānapoṇo nibbānapabbhāro”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant who develops and cultivates the four absorptions slants, slopes, and inclines to extinguishment.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.9"
msgid "Dvādasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:2.10"
msgid "Gaṅgāpeyyālavaggo paṭhamo. "
msgstr "(To be expanded for each of the different rivers as in SN 45.91–102.) "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:3.1"
msgid "Cha pācīnato ninnā, "
msgstr "Six on slanting to the east, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:3.2"
msgid "cha ninnā ca samuddato; "
msgstr "and six on slanting to the ocean; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:3.3"
msgid "Dvete cha dvādasa honti, "
msgstr "these two sixes make twelve, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn53.1-12:3.4"
msgid "vaggo tena pavuccatīti. "
msgstr "and that’s how this chapter is recited."

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
